id: monica-agent-tool-contracts
title: Make generated agent tool contracts executable and mutation-safe
description: "Make every generated agent tool correspond to an executable Monica CLI leaf, preserve positional and inherited inputs, and classify every Monica data mutation as unsafe for read-only planners."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[8]: agent-ux,anthropic,api-contracts,command-catalog,mcp,openai,read-only-safety,typescript
created_at: "2026-07-23T04:53:29.138Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T05:36:34.394Z"
deadline: "2026-07-30T04:53:29.138Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T05:27:35.402Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "OpenAI and Anthropic exports include every executable leaf command exactly once; Required and optional positional arguments appear in tool input schemas with stable names and correct requiredness; Inherited global and parent options remain available without duplicate parameters; Every remote write command is excluded from agent-tools safe-commands, including introduction, avatar, document upload, and photo upload; All exported contracts validate against documented schemas in JSON and default TOON output; Repo-wide release gates retain exact 100/100/100/100 coverage, 100 percent docstrings, <=300 code lines, and zero dependency vulnerabilities"
definition_of_ready: Authoritative Monica 4.x route source and current generated command tree inspected; duplicate-safe all-status pm search and fuzzy dedupe audit completed; private settings remain outside the repository in read-only mode.
value: Agents can invoke Monica deterministically without missing required IDs or being told that write operations are safe.
impact: "Prevents unsafe mutation planning and unlocks complete OpenAI, Anthropic, and MCP tool execution for all Monica resources."
outcome: Every generated tool is executable from its schema and every safe-command entry is guaranteed not to mutate Monica data.
why_now: Live API research exposed contract errors in the agent interface even though endpoint parity is complete.
parent: monica-platform
reviewer: github-bots
risk: high
confidence: 95
sprint: 2026-07-agent-contracts
release: 2026.7.23
reporter: codex-root
severity: high
environment: monica-cli 2026.7.22; Monica 4.x 32028ce; Bun 1.3.11; Node >=22.13
repro_steps: Run monica --json info command-catalog and observe contacts introduction/avatar plus documents/photos upload marked read; run monica --json agent-tools openai and observe argument-only leaf tools/required positional IDs are absent.
resolution: "OpenAI, Anthropic, and MCP exporters now emit all 233 unique executable leaves with positional, inherited, typed, and authoritative mandatory inputs; drain-aware output prevents truncation; safe-commands excludes Monica mutations, setup/config changes, uploads, and local exports."
expected_result: Agent exports contain every executable leaf with complete arguments/options and classify all Monica mutations as writes.
actual_result: "All 233 tools are unique and executable across three exporters, all 124 safe commands are non-mutating, large JSON parses successfully, and exact 100/100/100/100 plus live read-only acceptance passes."
affected_version: 2026.7.22
fixed_version: 2026.7.23
component: agent command contracts
regression: false
customer_impact: Agent planners can generate unexecutable commands or select mutating commands from the purported read-only allow-list.
