comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:53:29.138Z",codex-root,"Authoritative Monica 4.x branch remains pinned at 32028ce with 35 mapped resources and 172 endpoints. The local instance is unavailable at bootstrap due to Cloudflare trust-proxy loading, so research used official source plus local deterministic catalogs and only GET probes."
  "2026-07-23T05:02:39.031Z",codex-root,"Implementation milestone: all 233 executable leaves are exported exactly once across OpenAI, Anthropic, and MCP. Positional arguments, inherited options, Commander mandatory inputs, boolean flags, and drain-aware large output are verified. The safe allow-list contains 124 commands and excludes all identified remote/local mutations. Vitest is exact 100/100/100/100 across 845 tests."
  "2026-07-23T05:27:33.979Z",codex-root,"Final acceptance: pm linked-test execution passed focused 26 tests, live read-only E2E (95 total, 42 pass, 53 expected infrastructure failures, zero fail, five writes blocked), and full release verification (845 tests exact 100/100/100/100, 273 help checks, package smoke, audits). Latest @unbrained/pm-cli and pm-changelog are both 2026.7.22, including the managed project extension."
  "2026-07-23T05:33:49.168Z",codex-root,"PR #63 exact-head CI diagnosis: Bun validation correctly rejected the changelog after master cut release 2026.7.22 while this branch was open. Merged current master, regenerated CHANGELOG.md with pm-changelog 2026.7.22, and reran bun run verify:release successfully at the synchronized state. This is expected stale-generated-artifact detection, not a pm-cli defect."
  "2026-07-23T05:36:34.393Z",codex-root,"Hosted CI root cause: pm-changelog partitions items using Git release tags. Fetching origin/master alone did not fetch the newly created v2026.7.22 tag, so local generation temporarily grouped released items under Unreleased. Fetching the PR merge ref brought tags into parity with actions/checkout fetch-depth 0; regeneration now leaves only monica-agent-tool-contracts under Unreleased and restores the 2026.7.22 release section."
notes[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:53:29.138Z",codex-root,"Do not store credentials or live response bodies in pm. ~/.monica-cli/settings.json is mode 0600, uses default TOON, and has readOnlyMode=true. Preserve it byte-for-byte except CLI-owned cache refreshes."
  "2026-07-23T05:02:40.426Z",codex-root,"Design decision: tool schemas inherit global and parent options with leaf-long-flag override semantics, omit root --version because it exits instead of executing the leaf, and use Commander mandatory metadata rather than help-description heuristics."
  "2026-07-23T05:27:34.612Z",codex-root,"The live Monica instance remains unavailable because its Cloudflare trusted-proxy bootstrap fails before authentication. This is an operator-side server condition already covered by monica-server-diagnostics, not a CLI parity failure; no new duplicate issue was created."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:53:29.138Z",codex-root,"Endpoint parity is not agent-contract parity: a CLI can map every route yet still produce incomplete tool schemas or unsafe planning metadata."
  "2026-07-23T05:02:41.761Z",codex-root,"Real CLI pipes are required acceptance evidence for large agent outputs: mocked console logging concealed 64 KiB truncation even after structural unit tests passed."
