close_reason: Delivered lossless executable agent tool contracts and conservative mutation safety with complete local/live acceptance evidence.
body: "Research against Monica 4.x commit 32028ce and the actual CLI catalog found that OpenAI and Anthropic exports omit argument-only leaf commands and required positional arguments, while the safety heuristic advertises contacts introduction, contacts avatar, and attachment uploads as read-only. Harden the shared command contract so generated tools are lossless, leaf-only, schema-valid, and mutation-safe across OpenAI, Anthropic, MCP, command-catalog, and safe-commands outputs."
